Students singing leading roles at the Zhejiang University Academic Conference research achievements make people's brains open - Xinhua
Wash hands with air, judge diseases with tone, and search for the source of haze Precisely Last night, at the opening ceremony of the 2016 academic conference of Zhejiang University, a series of academic achievements with wide-open brain holes were commended.
The main researchers of these achievements are students. The research covers the environment, machinery, energy, medical care, life sciences, humanities education and other major fields. The students started with a curious idea and created many high-end inventions with application value, some of which have won prizes at home and abroad.
Biosensors: Your home medical examiner
The team of Zhang Di Ming, a doctoral student in the School of Biomedical Engineering, showed a biosensor on the side of a smartphone, half the size of a smartphone.
"All you need to do is breathe lightly. This set of instruments can initially detect your health from the gas composition you're exhaling."
Zhang Di Ming said that this set of sensors is connected to the smartphone, and after exhaling the gas, the health report will be displayed on the phone.
Smart bracelets that can detect health conditions on the market generally detect temperature, pulse and other physical parameters.
And this set of biosensors uses graphene as a new material. Its target is the chemical elements, and its keen "sense of smell" allows it to more deeply and accurately reflect the health of the body.
Smart operating lights: a doctor's high-energy eye
In addition to smartphones, smart operating lights are also used in the operating room.
This invention won the silver prize at the 44th International Invention Exhibition in Geneva, Switzerland this year.
Zhu Linjing, a master's student in the School of Optoelectronic Science and Engineering, and the team of Shin Junfei opened new ideas in the defects of traditional surgical lights, and invented smart LED surgical shadowless lights.
"Many diseases are not detected and removed at the early stage. They are related to the lamps used in doctors' surgeries."
For example, during the early detection of cancer, if the doctor can't see all the tumor tissue in time, the cancer cells will spread afterwards, Shin said.
This smart surgical lamp has four lamp discs, which enhance the difference of different tissues under light by adjusting the spectrum.
During the procedure, the doctor can adjust the light spot size, brightness, spectrum, color uniformity and shadowless rate at any time according to the surgical needs and personal habits.
This smart surgical lamp has been tried in hospitals such as Shaoyifu Hospital, affiliated with Zhejiang University School of Medicine, and Children's Hospital, affiliated with Zhejiang University School of Medicine, and has received good feedback.
Last October, the invention won the first prize of the National Challenge Cup.
Wash your hands with air: water-saving and cool
Ordinary people wash their hands with water, rub more soap, and squeeze more hand sanitizer, while students such as Li Qizhang invented a "hand wash device".
As long as we stand on the washing table of the device, our weight can compress the air out.
"It's like a pump.
The compressed air forms a fluid at the faucet, and is combined with water.
That way, we can wash our hands! "
The color reactions and bacterial residue experiments proved that the effect of washing hands by this method is the same as that of ordinary hand washing methods.
This device only needs to rely on our own gravity as the drive, which can not only ensure the degree of washing, but also save 90% of water. The whole process is completely energy-free, energy-saving and environmental protection.
Last year, at the second Global Major Challenges Summit, this invention stood out among many of the world's top schools and won the only gold award.
Chongqing Middle Vocational School is an enterprise's prospective employee when enrolling in a pilot modern apprenticeship system - Xinhua
Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that from this year, the city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship" talent training model in 60 middle-career schools. Students who receive the pilot training also have apprenticeship status. After admissions, students will be prerecorded as unit employees by the pilot enterprises.
The Municipal Education Commission requires that the admission and admission procedures of middle-vocational schools and the enterprise employment procedures be standardized, and that the dual identity of the middle-vocational school students and the prospective employees of the enterprise be clarified. In accordance with the principle of two-way choice, the apprentices, schools and enterprises sign a tripartite agreement. For apprentices who have reached the age of 16 and not reached the age of 18, an agreement must be signed by the apprentices, guardians, schools and enterprises to determine the rights and interests of the parties and the specific positions, teaching contents, and protection of the rights and interests of the apprentices cultivated on the job.
The pilot schools are encouraged to adopt the modern apprenticeship system and jointly carry out the pre-employment training and transfer training of enterprise employees with cooperative enterprises.
The pilot schools should reform the talent training model.
School enterprises jointly design talent training programs, and jointly formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, job standards, enterprise teacher standards, quality control standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot takes the education system as a pilot cycle. The internship time of students in the enterprise is determined according to the professional talent training program, and the internship in the top post is generally 6 months.
In enterprise practice, the enterprise group management model should be implemented. According to the characteristics of different majors, one teacher can bring 2-5 apprentices to form a study group to ensure that the students are proficient in the skills required for each rotational training position.
According to the arrangement, from 2016 to August 2019, 60 municipal mid-career modern apprenticeship pilots were identified in three batches in our city, with each pilot number of around 50 people, and a total of about 3,000 students (apprentices) were trained.
In accordance with the principle of piloting and implementing it first, and gradually implementing it from point to point, we will explore the establishment of a long-term mechanism for joint enrollment, joint training and integrated education of school enterprises, so as to effectively improve the skills of students in posts, and improve the employment rate and employment quality of students.
