South African doctor: Omicron is highly transmissible but mostly mild
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe the illness caused by the new omicron variant of the coronavirus is milder than the Delta variant, although it spreads faster.
According to the Associated Press, as the omicron variant spreads in South Africa, a group of more than 5,000 doctors in South Africa's Gauteng province reported that the newly treated patients they are treating have mild symptoms, such as body pain and cough, which are similar to the flu.
Dr. Unben Pillay, the organization's director, said he sees dozens of patients a day, but no patients have yet to be hospitalized.
"They were able to control the disease at home, and most people recovered within 10 to 14 days of quarantine," Pillay said.
He said this includes older patients and those with health problems, who would have been more likely to fall seriously ill from the coronavirus infection.
By comparison, he said, in the last wave of the delta outbreak, the new patients he treated "had difficulty breathing and had low blood oxygen levels.
Many people will be hospitalized in a few days. "
In the two weeks since the mutant omicron strain was first reported in southern Africa, other doctors have shared similar experiences.
While it will take several weeks to gather enough data, the doctor's observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the South African National Institute for Communicable Diseases, only 30% of new patients hospitalized in recent weeks are seriously ill, half the proportion of severe cases in the previous wave. The average length of hospitalization has decreased from 8 days to 2.8 days. Only 3% of recent new patients have died, while in South Africa's early outbreak, the proportion of deaths has reached 20%.
"At the moment, almost all indications are that this is a milder disease," Willem Hanekom, the director of the African Health Institute, said, citing data from the National Institute of Communicable Diseases and other reports.
He also said: "It's still early days and we need to get late-stage data.
Normally, hospitalizations and deaths happen later, and we're only two weeks into this wave. "
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are observing case numbers and hospitalizations while testing the effects of current vaccines and treatments.
Although delta remains the dominant new strain of coronavirus in the world, omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, including South Africa as the epicenter of the outbreak.
According to health officials, new cases detected in Gauteng increased by 400% in the first week of December, and tests showed that the omicron variant accounted for more than 90% of cases.
Education Review: What does it take to save abducted children?
If the famous public service advertisement is analogized with "no sale, no killing", then, in a good environment where there is no demand for "trafficking", the collective prevention and national anti-trafficking make the abduction and trafficking behavior unprofitable, risky and costly, and such crimes will not occur repeatedly.
Recently, the emergency publishing platform for missing children developed by the Counter-Kidnapping Office of the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security went online.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for the release of missing children's information and timely retrieve abducted children.
Hearing that this app is called "Reunion", I felt warm.
The new technological means not only have the name "literary and artistic" and are full of feelings, but also are properly applied, practical and effective in informatization.
The primary goal of combating abduction and law enforcement is to recover the abducted children, and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of the suspects.
The meaning of criminal punishment, from individual punishment and social prevention to legal education, can enumerate a lot of "big words".
However, before the abduction case is resolved, priority should be given to the safety of the victim.
The matter is prioritized. Under the eager purpose of "rescue", such as "whether abduction and sale of children should be carried out with the death penalty" and other widely held and controversial topics can be put on hold and discussed carefully; however, the matter of rescuing abducted children should not be discussed.
According to the experience of investigating such cases, traffickers are accustomed to stay away from the place of commission as soon as possible after they have been successful.
When the abduction operation is delayed by one minute, the child may be further away from the parent, and the difficulty of solving the case will increase by one point.
In this case, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with effective methods such as the "reunion" platform that directly help to solve the case and retrieve the child.
After all, "fighting abduction" is a big task that needs to operate the entire legal system.
The fight against crime and the protection of the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation, to the protection of the judiciary, and the rigorous enforcement of the law, all need to implement the care of "child care and support".
In addition, the prevention of child trafficking, from the family to the society, can also be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three rested at a railway station, and the parents slept, only to wake up and find that the child was missing.
A two-year-old child cannot be expected to have sufficient self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, it should be at least fairly protective.
Taking turns resting for both parents, or placing their children under safe protection, is the minimum means to prevent child abduction.
From the other side of the police's fight against the crime of abduction and trafficking, the party buying the abducted children should also be concerned and punished.
Individual wrongdoing is often just one link in a long chain.
According to the provisions of China's Criminal Law, the legal penalty for the crime of abducting and selling children is five years; if the circumstances are particularly serious, the death penalty may be imposed and the property confiscated.
The starting point is high and the maximum penalty is high. Under the general trend of "light punishment", the crime of child abduction and trafficking is obviously a crime with heavier punishment.
However, there are still many cases of abduction and trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people's concepts in raising children are backward, and their legal awareness is weak.
The legal education of this part of the population should be followed up simultaneously.
In order to effectively control the crime of trafficking, the official law enforcement cannot be relied on alone.
If the "market" for abduction is widespread, the abductor is lucrative, constantly innovating the means of abduction, and forming a "fighting law" situation with the law enforcement, the fight against abduction will inevitably fall into the mire of inefficiency.
Therefore, breaking the backward concept and popularizing common knowledge of the law will also help to eradicate the crime of abducting and selling and buying children.
