Vietnamese People's News Network - Gulf Cooperation Council to address common challenges
Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman's stops include Oman, the United Arab Emirates (UAE), Qatar, Bahrain and Kuwait.
Notably, this is Crown Prince Mohammed's first visit to Qatar since Saudi Arabia and its Arab allies imposed an embargo on Qatar in mid-2017, leading to the diplomatic crisis in the Gulf.
In the crisis, Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Bahrain and Egypt have severed diplomatic relations with Qatar and imposed a total embargo on them, accusing Qatar of supporting terrorist groups while maintaining close ties with Iran.
Diplomatic tensions have seriously affected the internal unity of the GCC and have had a negative impact on the economies of countries in the region.
Four Arab countries blocked land, sea and air routes to Qatar.
The crisis was only resolved at the GCC summit in January 2021, when the Gulf countries signed an agreement mediated by the United States and Kuwait to move towards "unity and stability."
Saudi Arabia has reopened its border with Qatar.
Saudi Arabia and Egypt are spearheading efforts to restore relations with Qatar through the appointment of new ambassadors in Qatar.
The Gulf Arab countries resolve their differences in order to restore relations with Qatar stems from the requirement that they must unite in the interests of all countries and regional stability, and aims to meet common challenges.
During the Saudi Crown Prince's visit to Oman, the two sides agreed to open the first direct land route between the two Gulf neighbors.
The 725-kilometer-long corridor connecting the two countries will facilitate the travel and integration of the supply chain of citizens of the two countries.
The Saudi Arabian Public Investment Fund (PIF) will invest $5 billion in Oman, and the companies of the two countries have signed 13 memorandums of understanding on cooperation worth $30 billion.
The Saudi crown prince's visit to the Gulf states coincides with Iran's negotiations with the world's major powers to salvage the Iran nuclear deal known as the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA) - an agreement that Gulf Arab states have condemned for not resolving the missile issue with Iran.
The Gulf states have always viewed Iran as a long-term "competitor" and viewed Iran's nuclear program as a "threat" to regional security.
The Gulf states believe that it is flawed not to solve the Iranian missile problem and not to take action to curb Iran's activities in the region.
In the context of the failure of the nuclear talks between the major powers and Iran to meet the aspirations of the Gulf countries, Saudi Arabia has held direct talks with Iran.
The goal is to contain the escalation of tensions in the region.
This is one of the factors slowing the economic growth of the GCC countries.
The upcoming GCC summit will be the first for the GCC countries since the end of the dispute between some member states and Qatar.
This is an opportunity for the GCC to re-evaluate the diplomatic achievements that have contributed to the restoration of the unity of the GCC, and at the same time to propose measures to enable its member States to fully cooperate in order to meet common challenges and contribute to the stability and development of the Gulf States.
Let the university spirit and the spirit of the times resonate together - Xinhua
The so-called university spirit refers to a university's long-term accumulation in the development process of a series of ideas and value pursuits, is the soul of the university.
From ancient times to the present, the university spirit is essential to the development of politics, economy, culture, science and technology, society, and even the progress of a nation.
Since the birth of the world's first university in the modern sense, the university has been shouldering a unique mission that is different from other social organizations. For our universities, emerging from the autumn of national distress, its spirit is deeply affected by the changes of traditional culture and times, and it advocates the value concept of "Ming and virtue, build peace" and the patriotic duty of "learning and power".
At present, the trend of informatization and internationalization of higher education is becoming increasingly apparent, and competition for education, science and technology, and talent is intensifying across the world. As an important "supply side", the enterprise of higher education is facing unprecedented opportunities and challenges in its structural reform.
In particular, the proposal of "Overall Plan for the Integrated Advancement of the Construction of World-Class Universities and First-Class Disciplines" demonstrates the confidence and determination of China to move from a major country of higher education to a powerful country of higher education, and at the same time puts forward higher and updated requirements for the development of universities.
How can we strive to become one of the world's first-class ranks in a relatively short time, accelerate the construction of several world's first-class universities and a batch of world's first-class disciplines on the basis of a certain gap, and achieve "curve overtaking"?
In addition to firm self-confidence in goals, confident pathways and confident abilities, colleges and universities should give full play to three advantages: First, they should achieve a significant improvement in academic level and quality of running schools by continuously introducing outstanding academic talents from overseas, learning to draw on the advanced experience of world-class universities, and secondly, cultural advantages, inheriting the intellectual connotation of Chinese civilization accumulated in 5,000 years, and promoting the development of excellent traditional cultures, in order to gather strength, shape brands and improve image; and thirdly, institutional advantages, give full play to the institutional superiority of the socialist country, strengthen the goal-driven, pool consensus and synergy, optimize the allocation of resources, and provide a sustainable and solid guarantee for schools to accelerate to catch up with the advanced level of the world.
In particular, we should realize that it is impossible to build a world-class university in thousands of schools. At the same time, each school must show its personality and characteristics.
The characteristics of running schools should not only have common Chinese characteristics, but also reflect their unique goal orientation, school-run traditions and resource endowments.
In the case of Zhejiang University, we pay attention to highlighting the characteristics of three aspects in the running of the school: first, highlighting the characteristics of innovative and entrepreneurial talent cultivation, building an integrated education environment that integrates science and education, and university enterprises, and forming a full-chain entrepreneurship education ecosystem; second, highlighting the characteristics of cross-disciplinary convergence, promoting the optimization and adjustment of the disciplinary system, creating an institutional environment with cross-discipline disciplines, and actively cultivating cross-cutting emerging disciplines and iconic cross-cutting achievements; third, highlighting the characteristics of the running system and social services, carrying out deep international exchange and cooperation, and accelerating the formation of the Pan Zhejiang University industrial and academic research cooperation system.
In this process, it is particularly important to always adhere to the university spirit and allow the university spirit to resonate with the zeitgeist.
For Zhejiang University, the "seek for innovation" school motto, the common values of "diligence, practicing morality, discerning, and honesty" and "Haina River, Enlightenment and Heavy Virtue, Open Objects and Former People, and Tree and Country" together constitute the latest expression system of the spirit of Zhejiang University.
This is an important guarantee for schools to adhere to the correct direction of running schools, constantly accumulate cultural height and gather spiritual strength, with rich connotations and far-reaching significance.
Among them, the "Haina River" emphasizes the spirit of openness and inclusion, embodies the mind of "the world's talents for my use", and manifests itself in the high-quality concept of drawing on the world's famous universities to run schools and educate people; the "Enlightenment of Truth" emphasizes the spirit of truth-seeking to good, referring to the university's pursuit of truth, and more importantly, to embrace the cultivation of virtue and the striving of personality; the "open-minded former people" embodies the spirit of reform and innovation, not only the pursuit of knowledge, the innovation of scientific research, but also the transformation and development of innovation; the "tree of our country" emphasizes the patriotic dedication, and
This series of spiritual ideas and value pursuits is precisely the soul of Zhejiang University, which has been running schools for 120 years.
"The wise listen to the silent, the clear see the unseen".
Chinese colleges and universities should further base themselves on the overall picture of the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics, deeply grasp the era orientation and historical mission of the cause of higher education, and accelerate the construction of a world-class university.
At the same time, adhere to humanistic care and independence and freedom, and let the university spirit and the spirit of the times and the spirit of the nation excite each other, thus providing an inexhaustible impetus to realize the prosperity of the country and the rejuvenation of the nation, and the realization of the common ideal of mankind.
