University students in Guangxi can take up to 5 years off-study to start a business - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency Nanning, May 19 (reporter Zhang Ying) The reporter recently learned from the Education Department of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region that in the future, Guangxi colleges and universities will implement the flexible learning system and relax the period of time off for university students. The period of time off for school students to start a business can be extended by two to five years on the basis of the original academic system, and the time off for starting a business can be considered as the time of practical education.
In order to promote the entrepreneurial innovation ability of university students, the Guangxi Education and People's Society and other departments have worked together to build an entrepreneurial platform, and build more university students' off-campus practical teaching bases, university science and technology parks, university students' entrepreneurship parks, and entrepreneurship incubation bases, to provide external guarantees for university students' entrepreneurship.
According to the requirements, by 2020, the area of innovation and entrepreneurship practice bases of all colleges and universities should be more than 3,000 square meters of undergraduate schools and 2,000 square meters of higher vocational schools.
The government encourages colleges and universities to set up innovation and entrepreneurship credits, and gives priority to supporting students who excel in innovation and entrepreneurship practices to transition to major.
College teachers should have at least two months every two years to work in industry enterprises, in order to improve the awareness and ability of teachers to innovate and start-up education.
The Education Department of the Autonomous Region requested the universities in Guangxi to thoroughly implement the innovation and entrepreneurship training plan for university students, and strive to enable every university student to participate in an innovation and entrepreneurship training plan while in school.
Colleges and universities should actively organize students to participate in various innovation and entrepreneurship competitions at all levels, and give financial support.
