Sun Yifeng, reading out Li Lanjuan's praise, said that Professor Li Lanjuan, as a pioneer in China's artificial liver enterprise, had achieved a major breakthrough in the treatment of severe hepatitis liver failure by creating a unique and effective Li's artificial liver system, and had significantly reduced the fatality rate of liver failure.
In this new battle against coronavirus pneumonia, the "four anti-two balance" scheme proposed by her and the team and the three technologies of artificial liver, microecology and stem cells brought with them have significantly improved the treatment rate of severe disease.
Sun Yifeng, reading out Li Jingliang's praise, said that Professor Li Jingliang had laid the foundation for innovative research in operational management, shaped the thinking of supply chain theory and practice, and revolutionized business models around the world.
Li Yuanliang is known for popularizing the concept of long whip effect in operations research management, and explored the measures to deal with this phenomenon.
Nowadays, under the pandemic and tense economic situation, the long whip effect is becoming more and more prominent, causing serious damage to the supply chain.
Li Yingliang's visionary research, such as snowballing, helps the industry cope with difficulties, thus bringing great social value.
When Sun Yifeng read out Zhu Lilan's praise, she said that in the course of scientific research, she found a breakthrough and innovative dyeing technology for the preparation of samples, which enjoys a high reputation among domestic and foreign scientific and technological peers.
She has been honored as a member of the International Eurasian Academy of Sciences and other important honorary titles with her extraordinary scientific and technological achievements, and has won her due high status in the world's science and technology temple with her brilliant achievements.
Chen Xin, acting dean of the Greater China Medical Research Institute of Australia, read out Chen Kaixian's praise and said that Professor Chen Kaixian has been engaged in drug research and development for more than 40 years. His outstanding scientific achievements and important contributions to the country, Macao, Macao University and national key laboratories have given him a high international status and prestige.
His positive role in promoting the development of Chinese medicine in Macao and the GBA fully reflects his sense of mission to contribute to the national pharmaceutical development strategy.
Yi Chengzhong, Dean of the Academy of Science and Technology of ANU, read out Jiang's praise and said that the major inventions and patents that Ms. Jiang had participated in R & D had accumulated more than 15 related to storage virtualization, navigation, file system and power management, all of which were highly practical and widely used, and improved the convenience of human life.
As an accomplished inventor, Ms. Jiang can often simplify high-level technology and theory to popularize the public.
Finally, Chen Kai first read his thank-you speech as an honorary doctor's representative.
He was pleased to see that the pharmaceutical undertakings in Macao and the GBA have set a good example: from the establishment of the first National Key Laboratory for the Study of Chinese Medicine Quality by the Australian University to the flourishing development of Chinese medicine in the GBA, the Australian University has played a huge role in integrating the outstanding talents in the field of Chinese medicine in the GBA.
In addition, he believes that the management team of ANU has the foresight to not only provide students with fertile ground for scientific research academically, but also to channel many talents with a sense of responsibility to the community.
