Education Information: Beijing compressed the proportion of specialty students enrolled in junior high schools in 2016 - Xinhua
On the 21st and 22nd days, the examination and inspection of specialty students for admission to Beijing Junior High School was carried out by the district education committees.
This year, all districts in Beijing have compressed the enrollment ratio of specialty students, and the competition for specialty students is more intense.
In Dongcheng District, for example, the overall enrollment ratio of specialty students in this district's elementary school to junior high school this year will not exceed 5% of the district's enrollment plan. The planned enrollment is 380 students, and the attendance rate will not exceed 10% of the school's enrollment plan.
Students with specialties in sports, art, science and technology who enroll online are eligible to participate in the admissions examination for specialty students.
In order to facilitate the students to participate in the inspection nearby, Dongcheng District continued last year's inspection arrangement, and set up one to two inspection sites in each school district, with a total of 13 inspection sites.
The test centers are divided by test areas, and the time periods are divided in hours. On the day of the test, the students will enter the test centers in different test areas to conduct the examination.
On May 23, the online list of students who passed the examination was publicized by the district education admissions and examination centers. Students can inquire the results of the examination online.
